cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SE 

The paper deals with the problem of network security, specifically the detection and classification of malware traffic using deep learning models. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of network traffic data (cs.NI) and the application of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) for solving the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of traditional, shallow-like models and proposes a new approach using deep learning, which can be considered as a contribution to software engineering (cs.SE).
